.DS_Store

# Benchmark (BENCHMARK_SPEC.md / VIZ_BENCH_TASKS.md VB-5..VB-8): the engine's own tripinfo/
# summary/FCD analogs are regenerated by `dotnet run --project src/Sim.BenchCity` and are NEVER
# committed (only the SUMO reference summary/tripinfo + provenance + small-rung replay.html are
# committed goldens -- see scenarios/_bench/city-*/provenance.txt and VB-8's "committed vs
# regenerated" list). Large rungs' FCD is regenerate-on-demand, never committed, per the same rule.
scenarios/_bench/city-*/engine.fcd.xml
scenarios/_bench/city-*/engine.summary.xml
scenarios/_bench/city-*/engine.tripinfo.xml
scenarios/_bench/city-organic-L2/replay.html
scenarios/_bench/city-mixed-1k/replay.html
